Plot density plots of the basic reproduction number

plot_R0_density.Rd

Plot density plots of the basic reproduction number

plot_R0_density(sims = NULL)

Arguments

sims

A data.table from scenario_analysis.

Value

A ggplot2 plot of R0 density over the scenarios explored

Examples


## code
plot_R0_density
#> function (sims = NULL) 
#> {
#>     plot <- sims %>% dplyr::group_by(scenario, sample) %>% dplyr::filter(time == 
#>         max(time)) %>% dplyr::ungroup() %>% ggplot2::ggplot(ggplot2::aes(x = R0, 
#>         y = factor(event_size), fill = stat(x))) + ggridges::geom_density_ridges_gradient(quantile_lines = TRUE, 
#>         quantiles = c(0.05, 0.95)) + ggplot2::facet_grid(serial_mean ~ 
#>         event_duration) + ggplot2::scale_fill_continuous(type = "viridis", 
#>         direction = 1) + ggplot2::theme_minimal() + ggplot2::labs(x = "Reproduction number (R0)", 
#>         y = "Transmission event size") + ggplot2::theme(legend.position = "bottom") + 
#>         ggplot2::guides(fill = ggplot2::guide_colorbar(title = "R0"))
#>     return(suppressWarnings(suppressMessages(plot)))
#> }
